gomodel:SYNGO_2180  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"An asymmetrical synapse (double arrows) made by a mossy fiber terminal (mt) with a granule cell dendrite (d) is immunopositive for the γ2 subunit. Particles also are present on the extrasynaptic dendritic membranes (arrowheads). B,\"\n\nFig.7: \"Colocalization of the α1 (20-nm gold), β2/3 (5-nm gold), and γ2 (10-nm gold) subunits of the GABAA receptor in Golgi synapses of the mouse cerebellum.\". Experimental description: Fig.5: \"Postembedding immunogold reactions are shown on Lowicryl resin-embedded rat cerebellum\"\nFig.7: \"Colocalization of the α1 (20-nm gold), β2/3 (5-nm gold), and γ2 (10-nm gold) subunits of the GABAAreceptor in Golgi synapses of the mouse cerebellum.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
